The state of elements on the surface of CDs-MgAl-LDHs@MnO2/Fe3O4 micromotors was analyzed by XPS (Fig. 2
                        ). Fig. 2a verifies the presence of elements C, O, N, Mg, Al, Mn and Fe on the surface of the micromotor. The XPS spectra of C 1 s (Fig. 2b) shows three peaks at 288.7, 285.8 and 284.6 eV, which were attributed to C = O, C-O/C-N and C–C/C = C, respectively. The O 1 s spectrum in Fig. 2c could be fitted into three peaks at 532.3, 531.7 and 530.7 eV, which correspond to H-O–H, M−O−H and M−O−M (M = Mg, Al, Mn and Fe), respectively [31]. The XPS spectrum of N 1 s (Fig. 2d) could be deconvolved into 400.3 eV (N–H) and 399.1 eV (C-N) of amino groups that were caused by the introduction of nitrogen source during the synthesis of the CDs [46]. The peaks of Mg 1 s and Al 2p from MgAl-LDHs (Fig. 2e and Fig. 2f) at 1330.9 eV and 74.3 eV were attributed to Al-O and Mg-O, respectively. In Fig. 2g, the peaks of Mn 2p were fitted into Mn 2p1/2 and Mn 2p3/2, where the peaks at 656.1 and 643.5 eV belonged to Mn4+, and the peaks at 653.4 and 643.5 eV belonged to Mn3+ and Mn2+. MnO2 could be further deconvoluted into Mn2+, Mn3+ and Mn4+ oxidation states. These ions with different valence states favored the decomposition of H2O2 to produce free radicals [31,47]. The XPS spectrum of Fe 2p indicates the presence of Fe3+ and Fe2+ (Fig. 2h), where the peaks at 725.2 and 712.9 correspond to Fe 2p1/2 and Fe 2p3/2 of Fe3+, respectively, while the peaks at 722.8 and 710.5 assigned to Fe 2p1/2 and Fe 2p3/2 of Fe2+, respectively. The presence of Fe3O4 was confirmed by the presences of Fe3+ and Fe2+ 
                        [48].
